# Z Security Rules

- Never commit or output secrets (API keys, tokens, passwords, private certificates, recovery phrases, .env contents).
- Never hardcode credentials or print sensitive values in markdown, logs, code, or generated artifacts.
- Keep secrets only in approved secret stores or runtime environment variables.
- If a value may be sensitive, treat it as sensitive and redact by default.
- Security discipline has priority over convenience and speed.
